<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-04T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-04T21:00:00-05:00" n="95" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3582: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-04T22:00:00-04:00">March 4, 1934—10
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 4—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>15. My telegram No. 13, February 27, 11 p.m. Official Paraguayan
                                reply to League Commission virtually refuses peace proposal, chief
                                objection as stated in my telegram referred to. Full text by air
                                mail.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires and La Paz.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>